genresAdvancedInfo.name: libyan pop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Libyan pop is a genre of popular music that originated in Libya and is influenced by both Arabic and Western music. It often features Arabic lyrics and melodies, as well as elements of pop, rock, and electronic music. The lyrics often address themes of love, relationships, and personal experiences. Libyan pop has gained popularity in recent years, both within Libya and in other parts of the Arab world.
